    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Multilingual NER\\n\",\"**NLP Project 67 of 100** — Extract entities across languages using multilingual transformer models.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess,sys,importlib\\nfor pkg in ['transformers','torch']:\\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','pip','install','-q',pkg])\\nprint('Ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"from transformers import pipeline\\nimport torch\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\ndevice = 0 if torch.cuda.is_available() else -1\\nner = pipeline('ner', model='Davlan/xlm-roberta-large-ner-hrl', aggregation_strategy='simple', device=device)\\nprint('Model loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"texts = [\\n    ('Apple CEO Tim Cook announced new products in Cupertino.', 'English'),\\n    ('El presidente Macron visitó Berlín para reunirse con Scholz.', 'Spanish'),\\n    ('Le PDG de Google, Sundar Pichai, a annoncé de nouvelles fonctionnalités à Paris.', 'French'),\\n    ('Die Bundeskanzlerin Merkel traf sich mit Biden in Washington.', 'German'),\\n]\\n\\nfor text, lang in texts:\\n    entities = ner(text)\\n    print(f'[{lang}] {text}')\\n    for e in entities:\\n        print(f'  {e[\\\"entity_group\\\"]:5s} → {e[\\\"word\\\"]} ({e[\\\"score\\\"]:.3f})')\\n    print()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **XLM-RoBERTa handles NER across major languages** with one model.\\n\",\"- **Entity types (PER, ORG, LOC)** are consistent across languages.\\n\",\"- **For low-resource languages, performance may degrade.**\\n\",\"- **For production, fine-tune on domain-specific multilingual data.**\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
